caption: Great southern cooking. Our server, Karla, was excellent!
Love Libby's.   I wish they would bring back the entrée size of the Shrimp and gritts.
Excellent New Orleans style food. Free parking at lunch.
Great food, great drinks!!.Loved the Mimosa float!
Everything was absolutely delicious! Bourbon slushie was on point 👌

The place smelled like the grease they were cooking with it was so thick in the air it was hard to breathe. Now my hair and clothes stick like that. Not sure why you would smoke bologna that was nasty. The sandwich probably would have been better if they left the meat alone. The French fries and the wedge salad is why they got one star. They were not busy I had to ask for more water. So all the hype leading up to this and to be bitterly disappointed. Would not eat there again. Also no parking you have to use a pay lot across the street😕
Is there a bad restaurant in Covington? Nope

Great food, pleasant staff all-around nice atmospher. Was surprised how great it was when I stumbled upon this place and couldn't remember the name, and when I searched it was hard to find. I kept looking knowing I wanted to try more selections. It's my favorite now...
The chicken skins are the bomb!

Visited Libby's for lunch and like always was impressed with the food. The fried green tomatoes were crunch and the bourbon onion jam went great with the cheese. The Chicken and biscuit BLT was crispy and crunchy! The reason for deducting 1 star was for the service,  it did not seem like they were that busy but I always had to flag our waiter down for attention. I will defiantly be  back but hope to have more attentive service next time!

Food was incredibly rich and delicious, and the bourbon helped it go down smooth. The menu was simply amazing. It's hard to pick a favorite, so I have to go back to try more of the dishes. Spectacular restaurant!
Great food and hospitality. Not only to customers but also to their staff. Definitely worth a visit, and then another...

Fantastic experience. Chef's specials are always fantastic. Great cocktails and bourbon. Really one of the best experiences in NKY. They have been amazing in Covid with safety measures, takeout, and even single barrel bourbon picks. Great fish options for fridays FYI. 1st place I take family from out of town.

Love the atmosphere of this place. Great staff, great food. Plan out your parking ahead of time; the lot by the building is only for customers after 5 pm and on weekends, and the lot across the street is reserved until 6 pm.
Try to always go some where new but seem to gravitate to Libby's! Good food and great service.
The best fried chicken in the cincy/nky area. Amazing bourbon slushees, and the fried chicken is fantastic. Love everything about this place, come on a Tuesday for half off!!
Great Atmosphere! Great People! Great Food!
The best fried chicken and cobbler in Northern Kentucky. Cheerwine bourbon slushies are delicious!
OMG - Worth every minute of the drive from Columbus! Both the food and the service are unparalleled within this genre!
Delicious and great service! The fried bologna sandwich is so good.
Great food,  staff and Manhattan

I absolutely love this place. They do the best fried chicken in the greater cinci area, hands down. Fried green tomato app is awesome, and a killer drinks menu. Big fan of the old fashioned and cheer wine slush. Their hot brown is another cant miss but be warned, if you want to do something other than take a nap right after maybe order something else. It will knock you out with the best food coma you ever did have.
Food was delicious,  staff was amazing
1st time. Cool place. We went w/ fried chicken, biscuits and gravy and peach french toast. Excellent meal. Reasonable price. Server Rachel W. took care of us. Plan on returning to try shrimp & grits.

I sent my friends to this restaurant with my warmest recommendations. I go their often. This recommendation is always successful. The dishes they serve are tasty and the team is efficient and cooperative. Whenever we eat in this place we enjoy a pleasing evening.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
Simply delicious, must visit!
Seriously awesome food and amazing service. Menu has absolutely phenomenal stuff and their specials are AMAZING.

agreed to eagle rare 17 year at $30 for 3 ounces and bartender agreed. Only to get a check with 3x the amount for $90, I understand it's rare thats why I asked if he could give me some sort of deal to which he said he would do 3 ounces for $30, after arguing about it I walked out.. Last time I will ever visit after spending a lot of money in this restaurant,  hopefully they shut down due to the pandemic due to our great Governor Andy Beshear... I can guarantee you I didn't order $90 pour of bourbon. 2 stars cause the foods good & no complaints.
Awesome food! Great Manhattans!
Excellent atmosphere, excellent service and over the top food.  Charlie Brown's, chicken or fried bologna.  All AMAZING!

This place is a true diamond!!! The food is beyond spectacular and reminds me of home cooked meals I had as a kid, while being innovative and unique. The bourbon selection is large and the house picks are always amazing!! Add the beer selection and craft cocktails and you've got a place to enjoy any time or day of the week!!

Have been wanting to dine here since forever (covid-19 delayed this).  Finally had the chance.  Was not disappointed in any way what so ever.  Staff was amazing (thanks Clarissa for taking care of us, you were awesome and your drink suggestions were spot on).  Have really been  looking forward to the food and this place for a long, long time.  Man O Man.  Wow.  Started with the Goetta hush puppies and a dozen oysters.  Wow, blown away.  Great way to start.  Must say, the citrus crème sauce for the hush puppies was pretty dang awesome.  The oysters needed zero horseradish or cocktail sauce to go with as they were that fresh.  But this horseradish is likely the best on the planet.  Oh so good.  Moved on to the Shrimp & Grits.  I don't know what i was expecting but it was not this.  I literally have a hard time describing what it was I experienced with this dish.  So complex yet simple, robust but subtle.  Absolutely amazing.  So savory.  Highly recommend.   Next up was what I had originally set my sites on:  The Fried Bologna Sammy.  The depths of the flavors of this bad boy is unsurpassed.  A real delight to see and then taste.  I just can't explain it any other way.  From the outside to the inside, as i sank my teeth into this delight, my senses were overcome with satisfaction.  So perfect in every aspect and really made my day.  Also had the collard greens.  Also Amazing.   Great visit, awesome date day for Wifey and I.  Looking forward to the next visit.  Fried chicken gonna be next.  Thanks Libby's

We found this place on a whim and it looked really awesome so we placed a to-go order and waited at the bar. I was very upset to see the chef come out of the kitchen several times without a mask on and wander around the dining room past all of the masked front of house staff. I work in the hospitality industry and it is very important to me to give my support to local businesses who are taking these public health risks very seriously. It’s our duty to our guests to keep them safe. I asked about the chef and was informed by the bartender that no one in the kitchen is required to wear a mask. This should be unacceptable for anyone who has the best interests of their guests and staff in mind. We were sad to leave without our food, but couldn’t stay or support in good conscience. I sincerely hope this review will find it’s way to the decision makers and that they will change their policy.
Anything with a biscuit highly suggested
Great southern comfort food and atmosphere
Chef S. is legit.  Atmosphere and people are chill.
I've had Denver biscuit Co. This place is far superior. Biscuits are hand rolled. Chicken is savory and juicy. Absolute must try for anyone living here or visiting!
It was really good!  Definitely comfort food.  Come ready to eat!
Great food.  Great local craft beer.  Extensive bourbon selection.
Was recommended this place and it hit the spot. The bourbon slush is a must try.
Very fair prices for their remarkable bourbon offerings, food is delicious, staff is very friendly
Comfort food served in big portion.

Great food, but not COVID safe (even for carry-out). No place to wait that's at least six feet away from barstools or tables, where facemasks are not required. Arrived when told for carry-out, but had to wait more than 30 minutes longer. (Which would have been annoying in normal times, but unsafe to wait inside during pandemic.) Probably complying with applicable laws, but not taking COVID-19 seriously. In the meantime, we'll be taking our business to restaurants that are trying harder. (Still great food.)  (EDIT: Good response by the restaurant below. There was good mask-wearing by staff when I was there -- 100% except for one worker -- and we are all trying to figure out how to manage this pandemic. I maintain that more could be done at Libby's, but they're not ignoring COVID and I appreciate the candor in their response. Adding back a star for that. Food was great.)
Excellent food and service
Good food & drinks($$). Friendly staff (all with masks). Will return soon.
Previously employed. The Exc chef Shaun is extraordinarily amazing in Southern crusine. Mr. Brad runs a family style atmosphere where one will be comfortable.  One will want to visit.

Soooooo good! I got the 2 piece fried chicken dinner with white cheddar mac 'n cheese and green beans 'n ham. (Tues special 2/$20) Diners around me had the Charlie Brown (take on the hot brown). Looked delish! The next table over got the three course dinners which looked awesome also. Can't wait to go back. You better bring your appetite!
Modern twist on southern classics. Service is prompt and friendly, and the staff are knowledgeable. Generous portions, so come hungry.

Dined out on the patio and had a great meal. The patio is perfect and really enjoyed sitting outside.  Southern style cooking.  I had the Oyster Poboy and my wife had the biscuit fried chicken.  Both great.  My kids also enjoyed their meals.  I also really liked the smoked old fashioned.   I had the bourbon mule and just thought that was ok.  Definitely would choose the old fashioned.  We will be back .
Good oysters, GREAT fried chicken!

Libbys was a small little garage diner that DID NOT disappoint! The wait was a little long but we were given on the house/complimentary oatmeal cream pies, they were delectable :) . Our waitress was tentative and even showed us the fried chicken skin which was BOMB. We’re from Michigan but if we’re ever here again? We’ll be stopping by Libbys- and you should too!!!
Neat place with delicious food, highly recommend

Libby's is one of our faves and I must say they do not disappoint!  I loved the smoky Old Fashioned tonight and I'll be sure to order it again.  Such a nice balance of sweet with a hint of smoke during each sip.  We ordered the oysters, fried chicken skins, chef's chicken thighs, and the cod sandwich special.  All were well full of flavor and super delish.  Always, always, be sure to get Oatmeal Cream Pies!  We were too full after, so got them to go.  My husband was already hiding them from me at the table.
Great burger

The employees are very friendly. We sat outside and had plenty of room between other guests. Our server was busy, but took good care of us.The burger was cooked perfectly and the sidewinders(french fries) were the best! Definitely get them! It won't be long and we'll be going back!
Yum. Great food and friendly service. Server and bartender were super friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend their fried green tomatoes and the shrimp and grits!
Great menu options and excellent cocktail selection.

Fantastic restaurant. First time here and got a decent sampling of the menu. The goetta hushpuppies were a delicious blend of southern cuisine with a Cincinnati favorite. Shrimp and grits and the Oyster Po Boy were phenomenal. And can't get enough of that cherrywine bourbon slush. Will certainly be back. Libby's is the real deal.
Amazing food and great service! We loved the Cheerwine bourbon slushie!
Food was good for the price, social distancing was in place and the service was good as well.
Everything was great enjoy everything about the meal food was very good service was good and drink was too 😊 thank you for great food

Amazing drinks, amazing food, amazing service. We came on a Sunday and had the most amazing service, before I knew I needed a new drink it arrived. Bacon was amazing. Our server was so sweet and she gave amazing recs. I cannot wait to come back!
Amazing cocktails and the fried bologna sandwich was delicious! And the most hospitable and sweet staff.
Great service friendly atmosphere

Great place.  First visit. Had the Wally Burger.  Super tasty!  The Gouda cheese and bourbon onions really increased the flavor.  Perfect size too. The fires hot and perfectly fried.  My wife had The Michelle My Belle salad.  It was perfectly balanced. The fried goat cheese and the dressing really enhances the flavor. Delicious meal and the ambiance and service made it a pleasant experience.  We’ll be back!

Consistently good food and a fun place for brunch. Sit on the patio if the weather  is good. Food is definitely not true southern, but rather southern-inspired midwest. They're known for their chicken, but those "in-the-know" order the burger.

Loved the fried chicken! Crispy and not greasey. Goetta balls sounded better than they were. Mac and cheese, greens and fries great. Didn't even try the biscuit, looked like a little hockey puck. Very nice waiter
If you like southern style fried chicken, you will LOVE Libby's in Covington!!! Great food and service!!! 😀💯👍

If I could have given more than 5 stars I would have! I ordered carry out today and it was a great experience from start to finish. The person who answered the phone and also greeted me when I walked in the door was a gem, super friendly and personable! The food, I'm speechless! Worth every penny and I will definitely be back!
Good cocktails and desserts
Love the Michelle My Belle Salad!
Better than grandmas fried chicken for sure, plus you don’t have to deal with grandma! Great food great service. Thank you!! And two thumbs up!
Great lunch menu and good food!

Friendly people. Even though we had to get it to go. Awesome people. The food was absolutely delicious. We got the the family chicken meal with green beans and mashed potatoes. Both my wife and I agreed best meal we had ate in a while.
Fried chicken skin.... Amazing. So rich.
Great food and service!
It was so good mmmmmm loved it.... Keep up the good work.

Inside the old Dixie Wholsale warehouse. Beautiful renovation of an old landmark for Covington. Good food and atmosphere. Service was excellent. Food was great. Their potato fries are incredible. I had the grilled bologna sandwich. Not your ordinary sliced bologna. Large slices like I when I was a kid. Parking was tight.
Great food. Fried chicken skins YUM!!

Ah, where do I start? The fried chicken had an amazing flavor, crispy skin & moist meat! Goetta Hush Puppies were my favorite! We just wished there were more! The crispy brussels & mac n cheese were also two side dishes worth trying! I am upset with myself for not coming here sooner! We will be back!
This spot knows how to serve their customers. Consistently with a very friendly attitude. The food is conveniently priced, always yummy and clean.
Delicious! Great menu, Current vibe, friendly staff, clean.
This is a fantastic place, great chicken!
Great southern fare and yummy cheerwine slushes. Loved the chicken and waffles. The goetta hush puppies were also delicious.
Great southern food, very tasty! Friendly staff and great service. The cheerwine bourbon slushy is pretty good too!

It was fine. A little small for the crowds they get now. If you bring a family be prepared to wait at least an hour. We waited a bit over an hour. The food is fine. People are nice just the wait times suck unless you go stag or as a couple.
Flavorful dishes, great atmosphere, clean with attentive staff. Solid bar choices. Goetta hush puppies? Yes please.
Fried chicken to die for and homemade pimento cheese is delicious

Had lunch with a friend today at Libbys for the first time. Had the avocado sandwich, very yummy. She had the honey mustard sriracha (if that's the correct  spelling)chicken sandwich, also yummy. Will definitely go again.
Delicious and the bartender was great!
One of my favorite restaurants in Covington!
Comfortable space, friendly staff, and delicious food! We ate here for NYE so the menu was selective for the occasion, but I'm looking forward to coming back to try their regular menu items!
Wonderful food- awesome atmosphere!!!

Very nice restaurant, the staff was very friendly and it's a nice place to relax and enjoy the atmosphere.  The food was great especially the Brussels sprouts! Those was Scrumptious! The fried chicken was very good and the Biscuits was homemade style, the grits was very good with a flair! I would recommend this place and I'm definitely going again!

Just OK. Was hoping for better and just being honest. Very nice but understaffed. Cold and surprisingly breezy which is only good in the summer.  We had jackets and scarves on. The tables around us were cold as well.
Amazing shrimp and grits

Yum! The restaurant is small so you might have to wait for a table but it will be worth it!! The chicken is delicious and oh the cocktails are too! You're in Kentucky so order the cheerwine bourbon slushie because it is delicious (even if you aren't usually a fan of bourbon)!
Limited menu but they do it all well.  My kids love it
Great southern food and awesome service. The might have the best motto ever "put a little south in your mouth" you can even buy merchendise :)
Ordered the 2 pc. fried chicken & it was really good. Juicy chicken- not greasy! The white cheddar mac & cheese was awesome. Overall great experience & atmosphere.

The restaurant is small and quaint and as soon as you walked in the smell of good food enters your nasal passage. We shared the fried chicken skin, deviled eggs, and fried green tomatoes. All dishes were delicious and enough to share. The fried chicken was delicious and the sides were okay. They have amazing cocktails as well. I Iook forward to trying it again soon.
The craft cocktail menu is strong, and Clarissa can make a mean Smoked Maple Old Fashioned! Beautiful bar, sophisticated yet wholesome menu items, and perfect service!
We both had fried chicken,  it was just OK. Not very meaty, fried to a very dark brown, but not quite burned.
Great food, great service,great atmosphere. Loved it.

I had the Willy Burger. It was really good, as were the fries and cole slaw. The place looks clean, even though it's a former warehouse. The prices are kind of high, in my opinion. Waitress was friendly enough. It was chilly with three garage doors open. All of us were cold. I'd go back.

I was told to try the shrimp and grits... yup! They are delicious. Cool little trendy city spot with great service and comfortable atmosphere. I like the little guy shops and this is a great example why. Hard to get menu creations like theirs at a chain. Give it a try.
Great food and service! Friendly staff and comfortable atmosphere.
Mac & Cheese is horrible but great wine & great atmosphere..
excellent as always.

Coffee was good. Limited menu; not much selection. Prices on the high end. Normal portions. Food were salty. Service was very good (shout out to Ian, our server). We were the only customer there at this time.  Street parking that was hard to come by. It's not a very big place.
Great fried chicken!

This place is a treasure and the locals are so lucky to have it. My husband and I shared the special and it was phenomenal!!! The meat was so tender. I believe that it was called a shortrib sandwich.  The fries were to die for. If and when Ireturn to that area, I will certainly go back there to eat. Service was also top notch! Didn't even blink at a table of 12 and she never made a mistake!!!!
Not worth the price. Could be a cool place, at a different price point.
Loved it! Someone finally figured out how to take the best part of fried chicken and make it an appetizer. Not all heroes wear capes

Excellent food and service.  The open air dining is wonderful when the weather is pleasant. It's situated in what once was a moving company, now repurposed as a restaurant.  Free parking is limited, although there a pay to park lots nearby. The menu has a nice range of options.  The theme is southern cooking and there is a lot of comfort food on the menu.  A very pleasant dining experience.  Moderate prices.
Great experience! Friendly service, wonderful food, love the industrial farm house feel and decor. Fresh flowers are a really nice touch. Food was excellent! Will def be returning! ❤️
Great food. Goetta hushpuppies, need I say more?
The food was very good!
Really cool bar with a fantastic selection of bourbon. Went there for a bourbon tasting of the new Kentucky owl release which included their own take on southern comfort food which was great.

Being from the south I found the food very authentic and flavorful. The sweet tea was actually Southern tasting sweet tea which is very hard to find in Cincinnati. This is my first time eating at this restaurant and I gave it a five-star. I think I found my favorite place that serves southern food. Atmosphere was nice waiters were very pleasant and helpful and helping me pick out what was on the menu. Also the fry green tomatoes are to die for.
Fried green tomatoes and breakfast brown made for a great brunch.
Love this place. Food was amazing. Shrimp and grits is one of my favorites, and they did it very well. Server was friendly and on point the whole time. Well done!
Always great food and drinks.
A little pricey for lunch. Nice atmosphere.
I love this place!  The food is delicious and the service is great!
Innovative menu, wide selection of whiskey, great food and service.
Great drinks, incredible food, cozy patio. Must visit!
Oh my gosh, treat yourself
Good food, great service, a pleasant first time experience!!!
It was ok, prices are high
Great food and drinks! Friendly staff!
Great shrimp & grits and fried chicken. Will definitely go back to try other dishes

Excellent food and drink - price points on some of the brunch items are a little high (i.e. it would be nice if I wasn't stuck only getting a $12 salad OR another item - what about a half size version of each to go with something less healthy?).
Yumm is all that is needed
Only decent chicken and waffles in the area only negative is small portions.
I had the shrimp and grits, which was delicious. Service was prompt and efficient. Love their drink specials too.

Wife and I both had chicken with 2 sides. It was very good she really like the black eye pea salad. Staff very friendly our server Clarissa made some very good suggestions about food and wine. We will be back.
The food is outstanding and the service was great. The goetta hush puppies are a must for any first visit.
Was so good, love the fried chicken skins, and flavoring of the fried chicken
The fried chicken is the best around. It gravy was really good as well.

We stopped at Libby's for Sunday brunch. The Cherrywine Bourbon Slushes are incredible. The goetta hush puppies are amazing. My wife had the house salad. It was huge. I had the oyster po' boy. It was really good. The service was terrific. But brunch was a bit pricey. Other than that, brunch at Libby's was great.
Great waitress and bartenders
Excellent food and service.   The staff was very friendly and efficient.   The ambiance is relaxed and I highly recommend checking it out.   You won't be disappointed!
Had the Fried Chicken Skins...they are amazing.  Kinda like pork rings but softer....all the best parts of fried chicken.

What a delightful surprise!  Stopped in for lunch with a friend on a whim. She had the fried green tomatoes with pimento cheese. Why have I never thought of this combo before?!? And I had the Michelle My Belle salad with blackened chicken. Again why have I never thought of this before?!! DELICIOUS!! My tummy is very happy.  It was such a hot day we had the bourbon slushees with Cheerwine soda. OMG, everything was just a delight in my mouth! Be careful with those slushees if you're driving. Otherwise, imbibe away!!

A bit of a mixed bag. I wish I could give a 3 1/2 star. Very casual, repurposed older building. Eclectic decor. Good bar area. Dining space somewhat limited. Parking on street only during weekdays, more parking available evenings and weekends. Appitizers: shrimp & grits very good, goetta hushpuppies were interesting. Main course:I had the salmon croquet sandwich--just OK. My wife had the chicken - excellent. Desert : oatmeal cookie cream pie homemade - excellent. Service: very good. I wish I had tried the oysters.
outstanding chicken, excellent sides, nice atmosphere

I was super stoked to try this place since I had seen posts about it on FB. Goetta Hushpuppies? Fried chicken skins? All the chicken?!? So I was very disappointed when everything I ordered except the sides lacked flavored. The Goetta Hush Puppies could be on point if the used the hot Goetta instead of regular Goetta. Even with the provided sauce options there just wasn't a lot of flavor. The chicken skins were over cooked and under seasoned. Even salting them after they came out of the fryer would have elevated the flavor. The fried chicken skin and meat had no flavor. The chicken tasted like the bulk chicken you buy from a food service store and would have benefited from a soak in brine or buttermilk. The skin again had no flavor. The Mac n cheese was on point. Add a protein and I'd make that a meal. Garlic mashed potatoes👌!  It was all over priced. If everything was 3 dollars cheaper I would have given it 4 stars instead of 3. Definitely not worth the price they are charging.
Great bourbon slushies!!!! Friendly service.
Good food great people
Good

A small space but the service was great. The perfect place to go if you're in the mood for fried chicken because the menu is limited.  The fries were my favorite part of dinner - large, spiral wedges with lots of seasoning.

The food was great and the atmosphere was awesome! The manager "Brad" or "Chad" whatever his name was asked my friend if we were about to leave yet.🙄 I didn't realize that there was a time limit on sitting guest and when they were supposed to leave.
Best fried green tomatoes I've had in a while. Nice atmosphere friendly staff
Nice place to eat and the chicken was good. It is a great addition to Covington
Excellent food, service and atomsphere.
Very nice atmosphere.  Good food and service.  We will definitely be going back.👍
Good food and excellent service. Slight twist on classic southern food.
Great place! Good food great atmosphere! Friendly staff! Try the avacodo sandwich and a two hearted while sitting outside! Thank you guys! Made my day!
Great place to meet and eat.  Enjoyed fried chicken skins

Food was awesome, but there were not a lot of menu options and it was overpriced in my opinion.  However the service was incredible and the good came out really fast. The layout was so aesthetically pleasing that the price wouldn't keep me from coming back
The people were great not a fan  of the prices and portions and I'm not a big eater
Great food and comfortable atmosphere.

Had the Kentucky Brown to help with a hangover and it was a ton of food. I elected to do it on biscuits instead of the English muffins, just because I like biscuits more and unfortunately, they were a bit too dense, which made them tough. Not my favorite goetta and there was a lot of it. I think I would prefer a runny egg instead of scrambled with this dish. My favorite part was probably the sausage gravy: little spicy, great sausage flavor and a nice consistency.
Nice place

This was our first time at this charming spot. We had the goetta hush puppies to start. They were nicely crispy on the outside and creamy and smooth in the middle. The sauces with it were tasty as well; a creamy, slightly sweet sauce and a remoulade of sorts. He had the chicken sliders and I had the shrimp roll. The sliders were the better of the two dishes. The chicken was tender and crispy with a nice sauce perched on tasty, tiny biscuits. The shrimp was perfectly cooked and sitting in just enough sauce to bring flavor without feeling heavy or greasy; unfortunately, the delicate flavors and textures were completely overwhelmed by a too big, too dry, and slightly stale tasting roll. Lunch and dinner menus are similar. They have a decent beer selection and a nice looking cocktail program.
overpriced, mediocre, atmosphere sucks, food is horrible, no parking.
The food was amazing. Lisa, our server, was incredibly kind and gave great recommendations. The Breakfast Casserole is more of a quiche and it is AMAZING! I will definitely go back!
Wonderful food, great food with a great atmosphere.
Yummy frozen cocktails & oatmeal cream pies from scratch! The peach mule & frozé (extra boozy!) are personal favorites! Try their fresh oysters, and don't forget the chicken!
Amazing comfort food, great atmosphere and excellent service...even for a last minute party of 8
Great Old Fashioned and incredible fried chicken!

Went there on a Friday around 5:30. Wasn't packed at all. My parents suggested it. One of the best places I have been to ever. Service, food & beverage options, setting, format, and prices were all exceptional. Would definitely recommend.
took my mom there for dinner, very cool.  food was fantastic.  had a wait of about an hour so we went over to Braxton and then came back to eat.
Layken and Ian are my favorite servers. They are so much fun to be around and made sure the food was out in a timely manner!

Visited on 5.4.2019. Nice cozy restaurant. Walked in and were told it was a 30 minute wait. 10 minutes later we were seated. Food was exceptional. Started off with a beer for me, the Cheerwine Bourbon Slush for my wife, and goetta hush puppies. We were very pleased. I had the chicken sliders and fries, and my wife had 2 piece with mashed potatoes and green beans. Wasn't certain about the pairing of pimento cheese with the sliders, but was surprised with how good it was. It also came with coleslaw; creamy, crunchy, with some vinegar zing. Very good. Fries are slightly spiral cut into a sort of crescent shape. They are crisp on the outside, with a nice crunch, and soft on the inside just like fries should be. The fried chicken, breast and a leg, had very flavorful skin and was hot and moist on the inside. I didn't get to try the potatoes or beans, but she enjoyed them. Service was excellent. The waiter was extremely nice. No matter who walked by, if they saw a dirty dish that was no longer being used, they picked it up and took it to the back. They also had nice bathrooms. 10/10 Would recommend.
Amazing food and unparalleled service
Great Fried Chicken as well as Blackened Shrimp n Grits. Will definitely be back.
It was alright. Food was ok for the price and Service was slow. Bourbon slush was good though!
Great comfort food!
Best food and service in Covington!
Goetta hushpuppies! They were absolutely delicious. Service was a bit slow, but blaming that on getting into their groove. The chicken biscuit had so much flavor. Pimento spread was esp. tasty.

Cheerwine slushie was incredible. The food was good but loved the family atmosphere. We were even served and seated by Libby herself. The entire family was working the day we visited including the children and everyone seemed to be having a great time!  Will definitely return!
Great food.

Many mixed reviews. My husband and I had a great experience. It was a Saturday night, and was told we'd have to wait 30 minutes for a table yet were seated with in 20 minutes. Our water was friendly. We ordered the hush puppy appetizer whuch came out quickly, and was very good. I enjoyed the Cherry Bourbon Slush which was a hit. Our main entree was the fried chicken with the gouda Mac and Cheese,  Black Eyed Pea cold salad. No complaints . 🍗🥃
Local, family owned with Great food and atmosphere, excellent bourbon selection

Really busy place on a Friday night but food and service was excellent.  Good fried chicken, green beans was good but little smokey flavor. Smoked gouda mac and cheese was really good but pretty rich. Will diffently be back.
Best damn fried chicken in the area
Super good brunch.  Nice bourbon selection!
Great food, great service, great atmosphere. Cant beat it!!
Had an amazing, flavorful Halibut n cauliflower special. Delicious! Hubby gave thumbs up to the Charlie (Hot) Brown! Kudos to Ian, our server. Definitely a cool place! Looking forward to going back!

A small southern gem in the shadow of a big city diamond. First, since it is Covington, parking is what it is depending on the time of day. After a meal here, you'll appreciate walking a block if you have to, since the portions are heavy. The inconspicuous entrance lends to a comfortable non-grand entrance feel. As soon as you get in the door, you'll be noticed right off the bat, since it's a small space. You can sit at the bar or a table if one's available. The bar is very attractive with it's live-edge wood and if you can't find something to drink here, you don't need to be going out. There is a decent collection of craft brews including Country Boy and a nice variety of bourbon.  Service was fast and personable. The menu isn't too busy. The goetta hushpuppies were in my mouth about 4 minutes after ordering and were delicious.The fried chicken was in my mouth shortly thereafter. Let's talk about that. Golden, crispy, and juicy. The batter wasn't overly seasoned; perfect for a hot sauce addition. Don't feel bad using your hands. I started off with a fork to keep clean, but turned cave man so I could get some of that crispy batter in each bite. I've eaten a lot of fried chicken, and this ranks up there with the best. The 2 piece meal came with green beans, fries, and a biscuit, but there are other sides. Let me tell you about the fries. They're like a marriage between a french fry, a home fry, and spoon. The shape invites itself to be used as a ketchup or a hushpuppy sauce spoon. Perfectly crispy and hot with no inter-fry zone mushiness. I'd go back for the fries alone. The biscuit was a biscuit and could be improved upon with regard to texture, but it was decent. My father had a fish sandwich and I wanted to grab it off his plate because the presentation was phenomenal. He said it was good, so I'll take him on his word.  All in all, Libby's is a solid establishment with solid go-to comfort in the form of drink, food, and service.
Try their burger. So good!!!
Good food for a very SMALL restaurant.
The cocktails are amazing along with the food. Go of you can. Will definitely be back.
Lip smackin good! Food is delicious and fresh. We came in kind of late but the staff was welcoming with all smiles! Libby's is a must!

This place advertises itself as a southern cuisine.  Southern of where is what I'm puzzled about.  I grew up in a rural area where that style of cuisine was a daily thing.  Fried chicken, macaroni and cheese and green beans is obviously …

The cocktails were great and so were the fries!  Definitely try the bourbon slush! The wait staff were friendly and quick. The only issue was the biscuit was hard and not fluffy. All in all I'll be back.
Overpriced but friendly staff. Food was nothing special.
Definitely the place to go for some Southern Comfort style food.  Amazing food, great atmosphere, and awesome wait staff... Not much else you can ask for.
The shrimp and grits were a great surprise. Different menu for Covington. Service was great.

A small rustic feel, great menu selection for southern comfort foods. I recommend the geotta balls and fried chicken sandwich biscuits. We visited during a lunch and were immediately greeted, ordered drinks and had food out in a timely manner.
Delicious po boy, goetta hush puppies and fried green tomatoes! Nice cozy spot with a great bourbon selection.
Great service and delicious food.
Always the best food and service.Well worth the wait.
It had a beautiful and inviting interior. I had the Shrimp roll, and it was delicious.

First. Bourbon Selection was amazing. Especially old stuff. That would get 5 stars!!! If you are only drinking read no more.  Unfortunately food was negative 5 Stars it was so terrible....  1) We were enthusiastically told the oysters were amazing. Got a half dozen. (Only ate 1 each) The outside of the oysters had not been scrubbed properly (maybe not at all) and had sea mud, dead barnacles, and black grass/algae??? (like stringy spongy totally unacceptable debris) They tasted like straight sea water. (later found out they were 12+ days post harvest) Chips/flakes of the shell were mingled with the oyster because they were shucked “personally” by the bald gentleman that convinced us to buy them... Later found out he had been a pizza delivery guy for 10 years before this gig. Oysters need to be respected and should ONLY EVER be served by kitchen staff, not front of house staff. (This is a big no no if you know anyone in the seafood business)  2) My friend and I both agree that the only significant tasting note on the fried chicken biscuit was “dirt”. Way over fried chicken skin that was reminiscent of a pork rind with no seasoning.
Great food & ambiance.
Cool atmosphere! Great food!
Love the chicken, wonderful atmosphere, good price, try the vintage bourbons
Food was fantastic! First time eating fried chicken skins and it was so delicious! Our waitress was so nice.
Nice juicy chicken, batter needs some flavor . Waiters are very attentive. Nice bar. Long wait for one of the few tables. I would try again.

We wanted to try something new for dinner and  seen several articles about this restaurant. We had been following the progress and opening on Facebook as well. Despite the restaurant being completely packed when we arrived, we only had to wait maybe 20 minutes, and sampled the Cheerwine bourbon slush at the bar. Delicious. The restaurant has a very homey feel, and you are instantly comfortable. We had the goetta hush puppies for an app, and the Willy burgers for dinner. So, so good! If you love goetta, you will not be disappointed with the hush puppies. We interacted with probably 6 different staff members and every single one of them were polite and just geniunely happy. It was such a wonderful experience. We will definitely be back.
Outstanding food and drinks. The Cheerwine bourbon slushiesnare awesome. Atmosphere is great. We will be back soon!
Loved it!  So personable and friendly! Food was outstanding.  Drinks (cheerwine bourbon slush and much more) were amazing.  Atmosphere can’t be beat❤️❤️❤️

The drinks here were amazing, and the food was OK. I got a Caesar salad with shrimp and the shrimp was amazing, but the salad was like straight out of a salad kit from Kroger. Also, the size was so SMALL, especially for  a salad and especially for the price. I may come again to try something else, but it was so crowded and hectic that I'm not sure.

Libby’s Southern Comfort takes away any indecision you may have when ordering from a menu with vast options. Instead they narrow down the selections to the best south of the Mason Dixon line culinary delites. From the staple of grandmas home cooked fried chicken, to the incredible goetta hush puppies, or the filling & pleasing buttermilk biscuit chicken sliders, they have your Dixieland pallet covered. Stop in, grab an adult smoothie at that bar, and enjoy a truly southern dining experience.
Fantastic food, fries are very unique and chicken sliders are to die for. Staff is amazing!

An adorable restaurant with friendly staff, delicious specialty cocktails and tasty, homemade food! We tried the Goetta hush puppies 🤤, wedge salad and the Willy Burger. We loved the dressing on the salad and the burger was one of the best I’ve ever had! Can’t wait to return and try more of the menu and another Bourbon slush!

Food is so overpriced for the quality. Pork belly sandwich is the most greasy sandwich I have ever eaten and the chicken sliders have little to no flavor. My Bloody Mary I ordered tasted like pure tomato juice and had an old piece of asparagus in it, that looked grey. I was really excited about this restaurant when I heard it was opening but now I know not even the goetta balls can make me want to come back.

Do not order the pork belly sandwich... greasiest, worst sandwich I have ever had. Chicken sliders were dry and unimpressive. Always appreciate new restaurants in this area, but Libby's food was very disappointing.

Had a party of eight. Only one table could fit us. Not enough room in that place and the beignets were garbage. Towards to end we were rushed out so they could fit other people. Thanks for taking out 300 dollars then basically kicking us out. Won' t be back there ever again. I am from Nola and this food is terrible.

The shrimp roll and fries were amazing. The shrimp roll was loaded with shrimp on a soft ciabatta roll, and the fries were a cross between a curly fry and steak fry. Just delicious! Can’t wait to return to try the goetta hush puppies and sliders.
The food was terrific, servers and bartenders very attentive and great. Prices good for what you get. Fried chicken was awesome! We'll be back soon!!!

Not usually one to leave negative reviews, but had an unpleasant experience at Libby's. Visit was 3/2/2019. Arrived around 6:30 in the evening and requested a table for 5. Hostess said it would be roughly 1 hr 30 min wait. Around 7:50 we ask the hostess what position in line we were, so that we could close out tabs at the bar, which we had been sitting at since arriving. Upon asking, we were informed/noticed our reservation had been crossed out, and that several other parties had been seated before us. Hostess claims she called the name but no one in our party of five had heard. Manager sided with the hostess, but were told they would add us next in line. We were then told that a table of six was cashing out, and we would be seated next. We did not get seated until approximately 8:15. Food is great, and our bartender was very helpful with the whole situation. I had decided not to write a review, and just assumed that this was a fluke and move on. This was until I checked my credit card this morning. I had given the bartender who had helped us (unfortunately did not get a name) a $20 CASH tip, and crossed out the tip line on the receipt. I was very frustrated to see that despite crossing out the tip line, that a $12.00 tip had been added to our charge. I emailed customer service, who were very prompt and respectful, and they have refunded the tip that I was charged. Not a very good experience for us. *Will not let me attach a picture of the screenshot that Libby's customer service emailed me showing the tip.*

Interior is very nice. Bartender was very accomadating. The goetta hushpuppies were a nice surprise, but the batch I got was so over salted I couldn't finish them, even though I wanted to. Shrimp and grits were spot on! Our server offered the peach cobbler, saying it was just coming out of the oven. So heck yes, I gotta try that!! It was delicious, but cold, straight out of the fridge.
Wonderful "feel good" food. They were able to accommodate our group of 8.  Friendly service and great selection of drinks!
Great food, small spot. But the wait wasn't that bad.

Absolutely wonderful food and service. Will be back! Reporting that the chicken sliders are two so that was fixed since the last review I saw. We had oysters on the half shell, chicken sliders, and the oyster po boy. All amazing
Fair service and fair food. Waited a very long time for bar service.  Honestly I think The eagle is better.
Awesome food awesome atmosphere. We will go back.!!  Check it out
Really expensive for average food. The fried green tomatoes were mediocre and the black eye peas salad was over dressed.
Food was great, but I was more impressed with the vintage bourbon collection. Must check this out if you love bourbon!

Food was good but the portion size was incredibly disappointing. Chicken biscuit sliders was actually just 1 slider which was questionable marketing. The salad I got was good minus the fact that adding chicken to a salad was 3 small pieces of blackened chicken.  Wish them luck but won’t ever return and definitely wouldn’t waste the money.
Kara and I went to Libby's last weekend and it was fantastic.  The food was great, the service was great, and it was a neat atmosphere!  We would highly recommend it!
We had the Fried Chicken Skins, The Willy Burger, and the Southern BLT. All were amazing and delicious. The only complaint is the servings of coleslaw and fries were a little on the smaller side

Libby's is a small and cozy spot that I'll certainly be returning to. The bar was stocked with some great bourbons, and the bourbon slush doesn't mess around. We went with the fried chicken, chicken biscuit slider, goetta hush puppies, Mac n cheese and green beans. Hush puppies were killer, cooked perfectly and not dry at all. They pack a great flavor punch on their own and the sauces take it to the next level. Next time I'm going for the fried green tomatoes AND the hush puppies. Chicken breading was great, and since it's cooked to order, every piece was super tender, juicy and flavorful. Is it better than the eagle? I can't say they are a comparable product, but both have unique great taste. The biscuits were perfect, and the Mac n cheese while cold still tasted like the good times. The green beans were a pleasant surprise, thicker cut and seasoned perfectly. They unfortunately we're also cold, but that's a problem easily corrected as the restaurant finds it's groove. Friendly staff, fast service and a great first impression.

We haven’t eaten here yet but can’t wait to make it one of our go to restaurants since Inspirado closed!  We love Covington and the menu looks Fabulous!!  We’re all about second chances so can’t wait to try this!!  Good luck!!
